Portugal to Raise Value-Added Tax at Restaurants, Diario Reports

-- B y   J o a o   L i m a
-- 
2011-10-11T07:35:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-11/portugal-to-raise-value-added-tax-at-restaurants-diario-reports.html
The Portuguese government plans to
raise the valued-added tax rate charged at restaurants to 23
percent from 13 percent, Diario Economico reported, citing a
preliminary version of the 2012 budget proposal.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joao Lima at 
 jlima1@bloomberg.net  